00:18:39,818 --> 00:18:42,150
I work at the medical compound in Mgambo.
I'm a doctor.

250
00:18:42,254 --> 00:18:44,154
You are British.

251
00:18:44,256 --> 00:18:46,781
Brit- Uh, well-
I'm Scottish.

252
00:18:46,892 --> 00:18:48,951
I'm Scottish.

253
00:18:49,061 --> 00:18:51,325
- Scottish?. [ Laughing ]
- Yeah.

254
00:18:51,430 --> 00:18:54,991
Why didn'tyou say so?.
I fought with the Scots against the Mau Mau.

255
00:18:55,100 --> 00:18:57,000
Great soldiers.
Very brave.

256
00:18:57,102 --> 00:18:59,070
And good people.
Completely.

257
00:18:59,171 --> 00:19:03,130
Let me tell you, ifl could be anything
instead of a Ugandan...

258
00:19:03,242 --> 00:19:05,210
- I would be a Scot, my friend.
- Right. Really?.

259
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:08,336
[ Chuckles ]
Except for the- the red hair...

260
00:19:08,447 --> 00:19:11,712
which I'm sure is attractive
toyourwomen...

261
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:13,978
but which we Africans-
We find this quite disgusting.

262
00:19:14,086 --> 00:19:17,180
[ Both Laughing ]

263
00:19:17,289 --> 00:19:20,520
Thankyou, Dr. Garrigan.
Avery good job.

264
00:19:23,362 --> 00:19:25,557
Hey, please.

265
00:19:25,664 --> 00:19:27,632
Would you let me
have this T-shirt?.

266
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:30,964
My son, Campbell,
he would love this T-shirt.

267
00:19:31,069 --> 00:19:34,698
- You've got a son called Campbell?.
- Yeah.

268
00:19:34,806 --> 00:19:37,434
Maybeyou would take my-
my shirt here in exchange.

269
00:19:38,477 --> 00:19:41,878
Right. Of course.
Yeah.

270
00:19:46,285 --> 00:19:50,346
- Ah. [ Chuckles ]
- Thankyou.

271
00:19:50,455 --> 00:19:55,017
Aha. You see?.
Nowyou are a general, like me.

272
00:19:55,127 --> 00:19:58,426
- Salute, please. [ Chuckling ]
- Oh.

273
00:19:58,530 --> 00:20:00,259
Now I must leave.

274
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:02,458
[ African Language ]

275
00:20:03,869 --> 00:20:07,270
[Man Shouting
InAfrrican Language ]

276
00:20:17,449 --> 00:20:19,508
[ThunderRumbling]

277
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:28,223
And I betyou
that's worth a frew bob.

278
00:20:28,327 --> 00:20:30,295
Yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

279
00:20:33,131 --> 00:20:35,099
Hmm.

280
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:38,169
I still can't believe
how you shot that cow.

281
00:20:38,270 --> 00:20:41,239
- [ Laughing ]
- You're mad.

282
00:20:44,042 --> 00:20:46,374
Um, anyway,
I think I have to go.

283
00:20:46,478 --> 00:20:50,141
- Do you fancy a wee drink on the porch?.
- No, thankyou.

284
00:20:50,249 --> 00:20:52,979
I'm okay. Really.
I- Nicholas.

285
00:20:53,085 --> 00:20:55,918
I have to go. No.

286
00:20:56,021 --> 00:20:57,921
Look, it's fine,
all right?.

287
00:20:58,023 --> 00:21:00,548
We're just havin' a drink.

288
00:21:07,165 --> 00:21:09,565
Oh, God.

289
00:21:09,668 --> 00:21:12,466
- I can't do this.
- What?.

290
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:16,969
My husband
is a good man.

291
00:21:17,075 --> 00:21:19,737
Oh, Christ.
I sound ridiculous.

292
00:21:19,845 --> 00:21:21,836
[ Sighs ]

293
00:21:21,947 --> 00:21:24,472
I guess I-

294
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:26,881
I guess I just need you
to understand why I'm here.

295
00:21:26,985 --> 00:21:29,180
- It's okay. I do understand.
- No, you don't.

296
00:21:31,990 --> 00:21:34,481
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

297
00:21:34,593 --> 00:21:37,255
It's just, sometimes...

298
00:21:37,362 --> 00:21:40,160
when you're married
to such a very good man...

299
00:21:43,001 --> 00:21:45,367
it's-

300
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:48,462
- It-It makes you feel-
- Like shit.

301
00:21:50,842 --> 00:21:53,242
My father's the same.

302
00:21:56,014 --> 00:21:58,209
And...
[ Inhales ]

303
00:21:58,317 --> 00:22:00,285
it's nice to be noticed.

304
00:22:03,955 --> 00:22:07,186
- Mmm. No, I can't. I can't. I can't.
- Sarah.

305
00:22:07,292 --> 00:22:09,522
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
- It's fine.

306
00:22:11,229 --> 00:22:13,129
- No, I don't-
- Sarah, it's fine.

307
00:22:13,231 --> 00:22:15,131
Don't, please.
Please.

308
00:22:29,081 --> 00:22:31,982
[ Exhales ]

309
00:22:38,924 --> 00:22:41,188
[Knocking]

310
00:22:41,293 --> 00:22:43,227
[David]
Nicholas.

311
00:22:43,328 --> 00:22:45,228
[Knocking]

312
00:22:45,330 --> 00:22:48,822
- Nicholas, there are some people here to see you.
- [ Murmurs ]

313
00:22:48,934 --> 00:22:52,495
Be, um,
right there, David.

314
00:22:52,604 --> 00:22:54,504
Right. Right.

315
00:22:55,807 --> 00:22:58,776
[Footsteps ]

316
00:22:58,877 --> 00:23:01,368
- Good morning, Dr. Garrigan.
- Morning.

317
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,744
My name is Jonah Wasswa,
Minister of Health here in Uganda.

318
00:23:03,849 --> 00:23:07,080
I've beensent byHis Excellency,
PresidentAmin.

319
00:23:07,185 --> 00:23:10,746
- There is something he would like
to askyou in person.
- Wh-What?.

320
00:23:10,856 --> 00:23:13,290
Sarah?

321
00:23:13,392 --> 00:23:15,292
Oh, hey. Listen.

322
00:23:15,394 --> 00:23:18,124
Why don't you tell David
to rearrange the field trip for Friday?.

323
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:20,425
All right?. I'll be back
as soon as I can.

324
00:23:20,532 --> 00:23:24,127
He probablyjust wants me to retie his bandages.
Okay, I'll seeyou later.

325
00:23:33,311 --> 00:23:35,802
My name is Masanga.

326
00:23:35,914 --> 00:23:38,405
Nice to meetyou.
I'm Nicholas.

327
00:23:38,517 --> 00:23:41,247
Pleased to meetyou,
Mr. Nicholas.

328
00:23:41,353 --> 00:23:43,787
Welcome
to the president's car.

329
00:23:43,889 --> 00:23:45,948
[ Cheering, Shouting ]

330
00:23:49,194 --> 00:23:51,628
- [Masanga ] Theythinkyou are the president.
- Eh?.

331
00:23:51,730 --> 00:23:55,791
- They thinkyou are the president.
- [Woman Shouts ]

332
00:24:03,208 --> 00:24:05,676
- [ Shouting ]
- [Whistle Blowing]

333
00:24:10,715 --> 00:24:13,275
[ Shouting ]

334
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:16,912
[ Whistle Blowing]

335
00:24:18,790 --> 00:24:22,624
[Man Singing Rock ]

336
00:24:31,536 --> 00:24:33,766
[ Continues ]

337
00:24:57,128 --> 00:24:59,096
-  [Fades Out ]
- The president's house.

338
00:25:04,269 --> 00:25:06,533
- Please sit down.
- [ Clears Throat ]

339
00:25:06,638 --> 00:25:08,697
His Excellency
will be with you in a moment.

340
00:25:08,807 --> 00:25:13,403
- And who's this?.
- Oh. Dr.Junju, the previous incumbent.

341
00:25:13,512 --> 00:25:16,709
- Ofwhat?.
- [Amin, Shouting] Ofrthe post...

342
00:25:16,815 --> 00:25:19,375
[ Normal Voice ]
of personal physician to the president.

343
00:25:20,452 --> 00:25:22,215
Hold on to your guns!

344
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:24,515
Everyone!
Hold on to your guns!

345
00:25:24,623 --> 00:25:27,558
[ Laughing ]

346
00:25:27,659 --> 00:25:30,219
- Good to see you again, Dr. Garrigan.
- You too.

347
00:25:30,328 --> 00:25:34,594
You see,Jonah?. This is the sort of man
a president needs around him-

348
00:25:34,699 --> 00:25:37,327
someone who is not afraid
to speak his mind.

349
00:25:39,137 --> 00:25:41,332
So, what doyou say,
Nicholas?.

350
00:25:41,439 --> 00:25:44,203
Will you take the job?.

351
00:25:44,309 --> 00:25:46,209
Wha- I'm sorry.
Um-

352
00:25:46,311 --> 00:25:49,803
- You want me to beyour physician?.
- Mmm.

353
00:25:49,915 --> 00:25:54,784
- Doyou want to be of service
to Uganda, Dr. Garrigan?.
- Yes, I do.

354
00:25:54,886 --> 00:25:56,979
Then what betterway...

355
00:25:57,088 --> 00:25:59,955
than to look after the health
ofits president?.

356
00:26:00,058 --> 00:26:03,619
And let me tell you,
it will not be a difficult job.

357
00:26:03,728 --> 00:26:06,856
Because me, myself,
I am a man...

358
00:26:06,965 --> 00:26:09,866
- in perfect physical condition.
- [ Murmurs ]

359
00:26:09,968 --> 00:26:14,496
Also, I know precisely
when I will die.

360
00:26:14,606 --> 00:26:17,734
It came to me in a dream.

361
00:26:17,842 --> 00:26:20,402
So, you do not have to worry
about making a mistake.

362
00:26:23,081 --> 00:26:26,983
- I'm really sorry. I'm-I'm very honored, but-
- Nicholas.

363
00:26:27,085 --> 00:26:29,485
I understand.

364
00:26:29,588 --> 00:26:32,716
Me, myself, I did not
want to be president.

365
00:26:32,824 --> 00:26:34,792
But the people,
theywanted it so.

366
00:26:36,261 --> 00:26:40,391
Listen to me.
This is very important.

367
00:26:40,498 --> 00:26:42,898
Here, in Kampala...

368
00:26:43,001 --> 00:26:44,969
you will have a hand
in creating...

369
00:26:45,070 --> 00:26:47,800
a new health service
for this country-

370
00:26:47,906 --> 00:26:51,239
something that will help
millions ofpeople.

371
00:26:53,511 --> 00:26:57,447
I'm sorry. I really do have a commitment
to the mission in Mgambo.

372
00:26:57,549 --> 00:27:00,109
I'd be lettin' them down
horribly. You see?.

373
00:27:07,559 --> 00:27:10,084
Ah.

374
00:27:10,195 --> 00:27:12,959
It's thewoman,
the one I sawyou with.

375
00:27:13,064 --> 00:27:15,032
You want to get back
to be with her.

376
00:27:15,133 --> 00:27:18,034
- Well, not entirely.
- [ Laughing ]

377
00:27:18,136 --> 00:27:21,037
It's the woman.
It's the woman.

378
00:27:21,139 --> 00:27:24,336
Why don'tyou tell her
to come and be here with us?.

379
00:27:24,442 --> 00:27:26,842
Uh, well, it's not
that simple.

380
00:27:26,945 --> 00:27:29,038
- It's quite complicated actually.
- Why?.

381
00:27:30,482 --> 00:27:33,781
- Is she married?.
- Yes, she is.

382
00:27:33,885 --> 00:27:36,149
[ Laughing ]

383
00:27:36,254 --> 00:27:39,121
Ah, Doctor.

384
00:27:39,224 --> 00:27:42,284
Doctor, you-
you are very naughty.

385
00:27:42,394 --> 00:27:45,625
- Me?.
- [ Laughing ]

386
00:27:45,730 --> 00:27:48,824
Ah, nowyou are
even more interesting.

387
00:27:48,933 --> 00:27:53,836
Married women, they are always
the most passionate, huh?.

388
00:27:53,938 --> 00:27:55,906
- [ Silent Laugh ]
- Yes.

389
00:27:56,007 --> 00:27:57,975
- It's true.
- They are so grateful, huh?.

390
00:27:58,076 --> 00:27:59,976
[ All Laughing ]

391
00:28:00,078 --> 00:28:02,672
[ Sighs ]

392
00:28:02,781 --> 00:28:04,681
Hmm. Yes.

393
00:28:06,418 --> 00:28:09,046
I'm sorry. Yes, I'm sorry
forwasting yourtime.

394
00:28:09,154 --> 00:28:11,054
No, no.

395
00:28:11,156 --> 00:28:14,717
My carwill takeyou back
first thing in the morning.

396
00:28:14,826 --> 00:28:20,196
But, in the meantime-
Tonight, we are having a state dinner.

397
00:28:20,298 --> 00:28:22,323
Please, would you
join us there?.

398
00:28:22,434 --> 00:28:24,402
I'd very much like that.
Thankyou.

399
00:28:24,502 --> 00:28:27,665
You have a suit?.
Dark suit?.

400
00:28:27,772 --> 00:28:30,366
- No. No, I don't.
- Hmm.

401
00:28:43,154 --> 00:28:45,554
How much is this gonna
cost me, by the way?.

402
00:28:45,657 --> 00:28:47,557
It's okay.
It's the president's account.

403
00:28:50,328 --> 00:28:53,627
- Oh, can I just-
- [Man ] Hey! Stop!

404
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:57,190
[ Shouting
In African Language ]

405
00:29:02,741 --> 00:29:05,107
- What's goin' on?.
- [Man ] Obote's men.

406
00:29:05,210 --> 00:29:08,543
- They're everywhere.
- Really?.

407
00:29:08,646 --> 00:29:12,138
Yep. They're communists,
you know?.

408
00:29:12,250 --> 00:29:15,242
Mind you, Amin's
more than a match for them.

409
00:29:15,353 --> 00:29:18,151
He's ex-British army-
King's African Rifles.

410
00:29:18,256 --> 00:29:20,156
- Uh,Jamshid.
- Yes, sir?.

411
00:29:20,258 --> 00:29:23,750
Pack those up and have them sent to the
High Commission in the morning, please. Thanks.

412
00:29:23,862 --> 00:29:25,830
Yes, he's a little
unpredictable...

413
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:28,865
but he's got
a firm hand.

414
00:29:28,967 --> 00:29:31,401
[ Whispering ]
Only thing the African really understands.

415
00:29:31,503 --> 00:29:34,370
- Thanks,Jamshid.
- You're welcome.

416
00:29:38,543 --> 00:29:42,479
Yeah, up yours too, pal.
Bloody English.

417
00:29:42,647 --> 00:29:44,877
[Women Laughing]

418
00:30:05,303 --> 00:30:08,329
Hello.
[ Clears Throat ]

419
00:30:12,744 --> 00:30:14,644
Hello.

420
00:30:18,583 --> 00:30:21,552
Hello there.
How doyou do?.

421
00:30:21,653 --> 00:30:24,087
- Ah! Nicholas.
- Oh!

422
00:30:24,189 --> 00:30:26,157
- I'm so happyyou came.
- So am I.

423
00:30:26,257 --> 00:30:29,658
Please. Please, this way.
I want to introduceyou to mywives.

424
00:30:29,761 --> 00:30:32,525
Excuse me. Here.
This is Malyamu.

425
00:30:32,630 --> 00:30:34,860
She is my first wife.
She has given me five children.

426
00:30:34,966 --> 00:30:37,161
Hello.

427
00:30:37,268 --> 00:30:40,135
Andthis one- Nora.
She has given me three.

428
00:30:40,238 --> 00:30:42,263
Hello.

429
00:30:42,373 --> 00:30:45,467
And that here
is Kay. Yes.

430
00:30:45,577 --> 00:30:48,205
- This is Dr. Nicholas Garrigan.
- Hello.

431
00:30:48,313 --> 00:30:51,407
- He saved my life.
- Oh, wel- Really, I just stitched his hand up.

432
00:30:51,516 --> 00:30:53,711
- It was-
- Don't be so modest.

433
00:30:53,818 --> 00:30:56,378
I believe it is you
I have to thank for the T-shirt.

434
00:30:56,487 --> 00:30:59,684
Oh, right.
So you must be Campbell's mother.

435
00:30:59,791 --> 00:31:02,692
- Yes.
- It's a pleasure meeting you.

436
00:31:02,794 --> 00:31:05,524
Please come. I have to introduceyou
to some people here.

437
00:31:07,966 --> 00:31:09,866
Excuse me.

438
00:31:09,968 --> 00:31:14,268
- This is, uh,
British High Commissioner, Mr. Perkins.
- How doyou do?.

439
00:31:14,372 --> 00:31:17,705
Please, meet my good friend
Dr. Nicholas Garrigan.

440
00:31:17,809 --> 00:31:19,674
Andhis colleague
Mr. Stone.

441
00:31:19,777 --> 00:31:22,507
- How do you do?.
- Fine. Yes, we've already met.

442
00:31:22,614 --> 00:31:25,606
- Well, I will talkwith you later.
- Oh, right.

443
00:31:25,717 --> 00:31:29,881
So, uh, Dr. Garrigan, we've been hearing
all sorts ofthings aboutyou.

444
00:31:29,988 --> 00:31:33,583
Yes, I, uh- I gather the president
has clasped you to his bosom.

445
00:31:33,691 --> 00:31:35,989
Uh, no, no.
Not exactly.

446
00:31:36,094 --> 00:31:38,085
What doyou
make ofhim?.

447
00:31:38,196 --> 00:31:40,096
Well, I think he's doing
rather a great job.

448
00:31:40,198 --> 00:31:43,531
- Don'tyou?.
- Yes. He has some issues to be sorted out.

449
00:31:43,635 --> 00:31:45,728
But, no, he plays
a pretty straight bat.

450
00:31:45,837 --> 00:31:48,738
- Yes, definitely one of us.
- Anyway...

451
00:31:48,840 --> 00:31:51,673
it's very good to, uh,
have another Englishman around.

452
00:31:51,776 --> 00:31:53,471
- Scot.
- What?.

453
00:31:53,578 --> 00:31:57,605
- I'm a Scotsman.
- [ Clapping]

454
00:31:59,884 --> 00:32:03,115
Ladies and gentlemen,
friends.

455
00:32:03,221 --> 00:32:06,748
I am speaking withyou now
because ifrl wait until later...

456
00:32:06,858 --> 00:32:09,292
you will be too drunk
to hear my voice.

457
00:32:09,394 --> 00:32:12,090
[ Guests Laughing ]

458
00:32:12,196 --> 00:32:16,462
- Here is where civilization began.
- [People Murmuring] Yes.

459
00:32:16,567 --> 00:32:18,558
Here in Africa.

460
00:32:18,670 --> 00:32:23,539
Here is where the Greeks
stole theirphilosophy...

461
00:32:23,641 --> 00:32:27,008
and the Arabs took
their medicine.

462
00:32:27,111 --> 00:32:31,775
We Ugandans must be more proud
of this history.

463
00:32:31,883 --> 00:32:35,785
We are an independent
Afrrican nation...

464
00:32:35,887 --> 00:32:40,017
Iiving in peace
and economic power.

465
00:32:40,124 --> 00:32:41,352
[ Guests Murmuring]

466
00:32:41,459 --> 00:32:44,792
- Black power.
- Yes.

467
00:32:44,896 --> 00:32:48,696
J ust like all you people
thought would never be possible.

468
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:52,099
[Applauding, Cheering]

469
00:32:52,203 --> 00:32:54,171
And now we will go through
to dinner.

470
00:32:54,272 --> 00:32:57,867
The food tonight,
it is all local...

471
00:32:57,976 --> 00:33:00,376
special food.

472
00:33:00,478 --> 00:33:02,810
And none of it
is human flesh.

473
00:33:02,914 --> 00:33:04,882
[ Laughing ]

474
00:33:04,983 --> 00:33:07,451
This is my last.

475
00:33:07,552 --> 00:33:09,520
[ Guests Applauding,
Whistling]

476
00:33:12,957 --> 00:33:14,857
[Knocking]

477
00:33:18,129 --> 00:33:21,724
Dr. Garrigan. Please come quickly.
The president is very sick.

478
00:33:21,833 --> 00:33:24,802
[ Groaning ]
They have poisoned me.

479
00:33:24,902 --> 00:33:27,632
They are trying
to assassinate me.

480
00:33:27,739 --> 00:33:30,537
- [ Gasps ] Nicholas.
- Okay.

481
00:33:30,641 --> 00:33:33,075
I just have to examine
your stomach.

482
00:33:33,177 --> 00:33:35,077
[ Groans ]

483
00:33:35,179 --> 00:33:38,478
Obote's people are everywhere.
Theywant me dead, Nicholas.

484
00:33:38,583 --> 00:33:41,882
Okay, I'm just-
I need to do this. Okay?.

485
00:33:41,986 --> 00:33:44,420
- [ Groans ]
- One more. One more.

486
00:33:44,522 --> 00:33:46,854
- [ Gasps ]
- Okay. Okay.

487
00:33:46,958 --> 00:33:49,586
Okay.

488
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:55,891
Okay. I think I know what this is.
Let me listen, just listen.

